Certainly! Below is a script formatted as a form that accepts and saves user-inputted text. This script uses HTML and JavaScript to create a simple form where users can input text related to Osama bin Laden's leadership style and organizational tactics, and then save the input.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Input and Save Text</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: auto;
        }
        textarea {
            width: 100%;
            height: 150px;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            background-color: #007BFF;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #0056b3;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Input and Save Text</h1>
        <form id="inputForm">
            <label for="textInput">Enter Text:</label>
            <textarea id="textInput" name="textInput"></textarea>
            <br><br>
            <button type="submit">Submit</button>
        </form>
        <p id="confirmationMessage"></p>
    </div>

    <script>
        document.getElementById('inputForm').addEventListener('submit', function(event) {
            event.preventDefault(); // Prevent the form from submitting normally

            const userInput = document.getElementById('textInput').value;

            if (userInput.trim() === '') {
                document.getElementById('confirmationMessage').textContent = "Please enter some text.";
                return;
            }

            // Save the text to localStorage
            localStorage.setItem('userInput', userInput);

            // Display confirmation message
            document.getElementById('confirmationMessage').textContent = "Text saved successfully!";
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
1. **HTML Structure**:
   - A form with a `textarea` for user input.
   - A submit button to send the data.
   - A paragraph element to display a confirmation message.

2. **CSS Styling**:
   - Basic styling to make the form look clean and centered.

3. **JavaScript Functionality**:
   - An event listener on the form to handle the submission.
   - Prevents the form from submitting normally.
   - Checks if the input is empty and displays a message if it is.
   - Saves the input to `localStorage`.
   - Displays a confirmation message upon successful submission.

This script provides a simple way to accept and save user-inputted text related to Osama bin Laden's leadership style and organizational tactics.

